id: pm-9yfo
title: "History completeness gate: contract-driven test proving every mutating CLI/SDK action appends a history entry"
description: The append-only-history invariant (all mutations leave permanent JSONL proof) is currently enforced by convention only; add a contract-enumerated gate so no mutating command can ship without recording history.
type: Task
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:history",contracts,pm-cli,quality-gate
created_at: "2026-07-06T23:08:54.068Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-06T23:10:05.021Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "A test enumerates every mutating action from the contracts/register-mutation tables (single source of truth, no hand-maintained list), executes each against a sandbox workspace, and asserts a history entry is appended with correct op and author; item-scope mutations gate immediately; workspace-scope mutations gate once pm-klo8 lands (until then the test asserts the known-unaudited list explicitly so any new unaudited mutation still fails); adding a mutating command without history coverage fails CI; the invariant is documented in the history docs."
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: low
confidence: high
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-klo8,related,"2026-07-06T23:10:05.000Z",maintainer-agent,null
body: "## Rationale\n25k+ history entries exist because item mutation paths call the history writer — but nothing proves coverage is complete. A new mutating command (or SDK primitive) that forgets to record history would silently break the full-proof guarantee that any item can be restored to any version. The contracts table already classifies mutating actions (register-mutation.ts wiring), so the enumeration is free and the gate cannot drift from the surface.\n\n## Phasing\n1. Item-scope mutations now: create/update/close/delete/append/claim/release/copy/restore/comments/notes/learnings/files/docs/deps/test-link/plan mutations/update-many/close-many/history-redact/repair/compact (audited rewrites must leave their audit marker).\n2. Workspace-scope after pm-klo8: config/schema/profile/init/extension-state.\n\n## Notes\n- Assert via the SDK read path (history list) not raw file reads where possible, to double as an SDK-first exercise (pm-usfg).\n- Explicit known-unaudited allowlist mirrors the eslint-suppressions ratchet pattern: shrinking-only."
